WEBVTT

﻿1
00:01:03.271 --> 00:01:05.230
[baby coos]

2
00:01:24.917 --> 00:01:27.211
[baby coos]

3
00:01:30.715 --> 00:01:33.217
-[whispers] Ha-ha.
-[baby cooing]

4
00:02:40.618 --> 00:02:41.619
[gasps]

5
00:02:49.502 --> 00:02:51.087
[groans]

6
00:02:53.923 --> 00:02:55.508
[cooing]

7
00:02:56.592 --> 00:02:57.718
[gasps]

8
00:03:03.099 --> 00:03:05.142
[breathing heavily]

9
00:03:32.795 --> 00:03:34.797
[object clicking]

10
00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:44.640
[clicking continues]

11
00:04:00.281 --> 00:04:01.866
Where'd you find that?

12
00:04:02.825 --> 00:04:04.702
You promised you would quit.

13
00:04:05.286 --> 00:04:07.496
Yeah. Yeah. it's not
so easy. you know?

14
00:04:09.707 --> 00:04:11.542
Why are you awake. Charlie?

15
00:04:11.626 --> 00:04:12.627
Bad dream.

16
00:04:15.421 --> 00:04:16.589
Me too.

17
00:04:18.089 --> 00:04:19.716
Do you wanna talk about it?

18
00:04:22.094 --> 00:04:23.346
Put that down. please.

19
00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:25.306
Come on. that's not a toy.

20
00:04:26.140 --> 00:04:27.308
Come on.

21
00:04:34.148 --> 00:04:35.900
[sighs]

22
00:04:38.653 --> 00:04:40.112
What's goin' on. sweetie?

23
00:04:42.782 --> 00:04:43.866
Daddy?

24
00:04:44.575 --> 00:04:45.701
Mmm?

25
00:04:46.661 --> 00:04:48.746
Something feels weird…

26
00:04:50.248 --> 00:04:51.374
in my body.

27
00:04:51.457 --> 00:04:55.044
I think we should go
talk to your mom about this. You know?

28
00:04:55.127 --> 00:04:56.629
Not that thing.

29
00:04:57.213 --> 00:04:58.297
The other thing.

30
00:04:58.965 --> 00:05:00.049
The other thing.

31
00:05:02.552 --> 00:05:04.011
The bad thing.

32
00:05:05.221 --> 00:05:07.056
Something's changing.

33
00:05:08.808 --> 00:05:10.601
[inhales. exhales]

34
00:05:11.310 --> 00:05:13.145
You remember your tools.

35
00:05:13.771 --> 00:05:16.482
If you ever get nervous.
if you're ever scared…

36
00:05:19.193 --> 00:05:21.821
you start to lose control.
what do you do?

37
00:05:22.697 --> 00:05:25.741
[inhales. exhales]

38
00:05:25.825 --> 00:05:26.826
Flowers.

39
00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:34.375
-Clock.
-[ticking]

40
00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:38.629
See a… forest.

41
00:05:38.713 --> 00:05:40.047
[child] Bunny.

42
00:05:41.674 --> 00:05:43.259
And sweet Charlie.

43
00:05:44.093 --> 00:05:45.511
The bad thing…

44
00:05:46.012 --> 00:05:48.306
It's been gone a long time.

45
00:05:49.223 --> 00:05:50.558
You're strong. Charlie.

46
00:05:50.641 --> 00:05:52.393
So. you don't have to be afraid.

47
00:05:54.645 --> 00:05:55.646
All right.

48
00:05:55.730 --> 00:05:57.565
Hey. Is everything okay in here?

49
00:05:58.149 --> 00:06:01.402
Yeah. Yeah. Peachy.

50
00:06:06.616 --> 00:06:08.159
[exhales]

51
00:06:10.203 --> 00:06:11.996
[groans]

52
00:06:13.039 --> 00:06:16.292
I'm really hungry.
Who wants pancakes?

53
00:06:16.792 --> 00:06:18.294
Pancakes?

54
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:20.338
You want pancakes?

55
00:06:20.421 --> 00:06:21.422
I want pancakes.

56
00:06:21.506 --> 00:06:23.299
No. you don't like pancakes.

57
00:06:23.382 --> 00:06:24.884
[chuckles]

58
00:06:26.010 --> 00:06:28.387
Blueberries. what else?
Chocolate?

59
00:06:28.471 --> 00:06:29.472
-Chocolate?
-Yeah.

60
00:06:29.555 --> 00:06:30.640
What else do you want?

61
00:06:33.184 --> 00:06:34.310
[Charlie] Strawberries.

62
00:06:34.393 --> 00:06:36.103
-Coffee.
-Coffee? Black coffee?

63
00:06:36.187 --> 00:06:38.648
-[Charlie] Orange juice.
-Orange juice. All right.

64
00:06:39.899 --> 00:06:42.777
[tape player clicks. whirring]

65
00:06:46.197 --> 00:06:48.741
[interviewer] <i>Thank you so much
for comin' in today.</i>

66
00:06:48.824 --> 00:06:51.369
<i>How are you enjoying college so far?</i>

67
00:06:52.453 --> 00:06:54.413
<i>Uh. I'm having fun.</i>

68
00:06:54.997 --> 00:06:57.166
<i>It's busy.
Kind of more work than I thought.</i>

69
00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:58.417
<i>I'm kinda homesick.</i>

70
00:06:59.001 --> 00:07:00.878
[interviewer] <i>I'm just gonna ask you
a few questions here.</i>

71
00:07:00.962 --> 00:07:03.381
-<i>Kinda background stuff.
</i>-<i>Okay.</i>

72
00:07:03.464 --> 00:07:05.299
[interviewer]
<i>Ever used hallucinogenic drugs?</i>

73
00:07:05.883 --> 00:07:06.843
<i>Too scared.</i>

74
00:07:06.926 --> 00:07:08.886
<i>Uh…</i>

75
00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:11.639
<i>I mean. it's college. man. You know?</i>

76
00:07:11.722 --> 00:07:13.683
[interviewer] <i>How about
your father's blood type?</i>

77
00:07:13.766 --> 00:07:15.560
[student] <i>Do you know
your parents' blood types?</i>

78
00:07:15.643 --> 00:07:17.645
[interviewer] <i>You know what. I don't.
Fair enough.</i>

79
00:07:18.354 --> 00:07:19.689
<i>Where do your parents live?</i>

80
00:07:20.356 --> 00:07:22.191
<i>They don't. They died when I was ten.</i>

81
00:07:22.275 --> 00:07:25.570
[interviewer] <i>It says here you were raised
in a group home. Is that correct?</i>

82
00:07:26.070 --> 00:07:29.240
<i>Indeed. I was.
from the time that I was seven.</i>

83
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:32.159
[person] <i>Numbers are in the threshold.
but let's keep an eye on it.</i>

84
00:07:32.243 --> 00:07:33.661
[person 2] <i>Turn the camera. and it spikes!</i>

85
00:07:33.744 --> 00:07:34.912
[person] <i>Confirming here too.</i>

86
00:07:34.996 --> 00:07:36.998
[student] <i>Why do you need to know
so much about my parents?</i>

87
00:07:37.081 --> 00:07:38.541
[interviewer] <i>Genetic history.</i>

88
00:07:38.624 --> 00:07:41.669
<i>It helps us understand
and evaluate the test results.</i>

89
00:07:42.378 --> 00:07:44.797
[person] <i>Slightly erratic. but looks okay.</i>

90
00:07:44.881 --> 00:07:46.132
[person 3]
<i>We need to drop his levels to 5 cc's.</i>

91
00:07:46.215 --> 00:07:49.594
<i>The ad said that this was just
an FDA clinical trial.</i>

92
00:07:53.973 --> 00:07:56.893
[interviewer] <i>Half of the people
will be getting injections of water.</i>

93
00:07:57.393 --> 00:08:01.063
<i>and the other half will get water
mixed with a chemical compound</i>

94
00:08:01.147 --> 00:08:02.982
<i>we call "Lot Six."</i>

95
00:08:03.065 --> 00:08:05.860
<i>A chemical compound?
Like what? What is it?</i>

96
00:08:09.322 --> 00:08:11.199
<i>But half of us are just gonna get
the placebo. right?</i>

97
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:13.451
[interviewer]
<i>Either way it's entirely harmless.</i>

98
00:08:13.534 --> 00:08:17.371
<i>Well. how do you know? I mean.
that's why you're testing it. right?</i>

99
00:08:24.378 --> 00:08:26.547
[interviewer]
<i>My next question here is a little weird.</i>

100
00:08:26.631 --> 00:08:29.258
<i>Can you tell me if you've ever had
what you would call</i>

101
00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:31.511
<i>an authentic psychic experience?</i>

102
00:08:33.386 --> 00:08:35.389
<i>I'd rather not talk about that.</i>

103
00:08:36.390 --> 00:08:38.518
[person] <i>Okay. let's make sure
we're recording her numbers here.</i>

104
00:08:42.522 --> 00:08:44.148
<i>We've confirmed telekinetic activity.</i>

105
00:08:44.732 --> 00:08:47.318
<i>I don't like these questions. man.
</i>[chuckling]

106
00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:51.656
[interviewer] <i>Just part of the evaluation.</i>

107
00:08:51.739 --> 00:08:53.658
<i>Let me ask you again.</i>

108
00:08:53.741 --> 00:08:57.537
<i>have you ever experienced
any inexplicable phenomena</i>

109
00:08:57.620 --> 00:08:59.956
<i>that goes against natural law?</i>

110
00:09:01.123 --> 00:09:03.000
<i>I saw my parents die in a car wreck.</i>

111
00:09:04.085 --> 00:09:06.045
[interviewer] <i>I'm sorry to hear that.</i>

112
00:09:06.128 --> 00:09:09.215
<i>But what about that makes it inexplicable?</i>

113
00:09:09.298 --> 00:09:11.467
<i>I saw it a week
before it actually happened.</i>

114
00:09:12.009 --> 00:09:13.261
[person] <i>His readings are erratic!</i>

115
00:09:13.344 --> 00:09:14.262
[person 2] <i>Turn it off.</i>

116
00:09:14.345 --> 00:09:16.013
[person 3] <i>We need to unhook him now!</i>

117
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:17.557
[person] <i>Turn the camera off!</i>

118
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:19.642
[all clamoring]

119
00:09:20.518 --> 00:09:22.186
-<i>Get him out of here.
</i>-<i>I still see it.</i>

120
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:24.272
[all screaming. clamoring]

121
00:09:24.355 --> 00:09:26.190
[person] <i>Hold him down! Hold him down!</i>

122
00:09:26.274 --> 00:09:27.900
<i>Turn it off. Turn it off!</i>

123
00:09:36.242 --> 00:09:39.495
<i>My service guarantees
that for just three sessions.</i>

124
00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:41.622
<i>your nicotine cravings will disappear.</i>

125
00:09:42.164 --> 00:09:43.833
And all we do is talk?

126
00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:46.627
Sounds crazy. right?

127
00:09:47.837 --> 00:09:48.838
It's not.

128
00:09:50.047 --> 00:09:51.048
It's magic.

129
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:54.427
[chuckles]
Okay. I don't know. Mr. McGee.

130
00:09:54.510 --> 00:09:55.678
Well. call me Andy.

131
00:09:55.761 --> 00:09:59.056
Andy. uh. $100 per session…

132
00:09:59.932 --> 00:10:01.767
Yeah. that's a lot for my budget.

133
00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:04.645
Let's just try it. One session.

134
00:10:04.729 --> 00:10:07.523
If you don't walk outta here today
feeling better than you've ever felt.

135
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:10.943
with those nicotine cravings already
starting to fade. it's on the house.

136
00:10:11.027 --> 00:10:12.403
Now. close your eyes.

137
00:10:16.782 --> 00:10:18.284
Keep 'em closed.

138
00:10:18.910 --> 00:10:19.994
Good.

139
00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:23.039
Now. imagine the Darla
that you wanna be.

140
00:10:23.915 --> 00:10:25.166
Picture her.

141
00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:27.460
Smoke-free.

142
00:10:29.378 --> 00:10:32.298
And a beacon of respiratory health.

143
00:10:37.011 --> 00:10:38.804
Now. look at me in the eyes.

144
00:10:41.807 --> 00:10:43.267
Don't look away.

145
00:10:44.227 --> 00:10:45.686
No matter what.

146
00:10:47.313 --> 00:10:48.648
[neck cracks]

147
00:10:49.357 --> 00:10:51.275
You feel better
about yourself already. Darla.

148
00:10:51.359 --> 00:10:53.569
Healthier. More positive.

149
00:10:53.653 --> 00:10:56.072
You hate the taste of tobacco.
More positive.

150
00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:59.534
And that stale cigarette smell
makes you wanna puke. [echoing]

151
00:11:01.369 --> 00:11:04.205
You are done with smoking.
[echoing]

152
00:11:12.922 --> 00:11:15.550
[gasps. chuckles] You know…

153
00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:18.427
I-- I feel better already.

154
00:11:20.471 --> 00:11:21.472
What?

155
00:11:22.348 --> 00:11:23.432
-Wow.
-[clearing throat]

156
00:11:23.516 --> 00:11:25.893
Healthier. more positive.

157
00:11:28.437 --> 00:11:29.438
Wow.

158
00:11:30.147 --> 00:11:32.275
-Mm-hmm.
-Okay. um…

159
00:11:33.067 --> 00:11:34.819
Okay. I have 75.

160
00:11:34.902 --> 00:11:37.613
but I can give you a credit card if you--

161
00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:41.033
No. it's cash only. so that's fine.
I'll just take what you have now.

162
00:11:41.117 --> 00:11:42.201
Oh. Yeah?

163
00:11:42.285 --> 00:11:44.996
-Yeah. I'm sure you're good for the rest.
-I am indeed.

164
00:11:45.079 --> 00:11:46.956
[chuckles] Thank you.

165
00:11:48.666 --> 00:11:49.667
Wild.

166
00:11:53.045 --> 00:11:54.130
Take care.

167
00:11:59.844 --> 00:12:03.014
[gasping]

168
00:12:10.188 --> 00:12:12.190
[groans]

169
00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:29.707
[student] Ew.

170
00:12:29.790 --> 00:12:31.125
Nice work. goober.

171
00:12:33.711 --> 00:12:35.338
[teacher]
How is it goin' over here. Gavin?

172
00:12:35.421 --> 00:12:38.090
-Weird girl killed our frog.
-It was already dead.

173
00:12:38.174 --> 00:12:40.134
Yeah. but now it's extra dead.

174
00:12:40.718 --> 00:12:42.136
It's okay. Charlie.

175
00:12:42.637 --> 00:12:44.472
A quick Google search will show you

176
00:12:44.555 --> 00:12:46.641
all the frog guts you want
dissected perfectly.

177
00:12:46.724 --> 00:12:49.060
We don't even need to
do this anymore.

178
00:12:49.143 --> 00:12:50.436
I don't have Google.

179
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:53.648
[students laughing. snickering]

180
00:12:53.731 --> 00:12:55.024
Quiet. class.

181
00:12:56.275 --> 00:12:57.985
I forgot. Sorry.

182
00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:03.115
You ever go to the public library?
You can use the computers there.

183
00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:05.910
Too much screen time can cause
health problems in children.

184
00:13:05.993 --> 00:13:06.994
like insomnia.

185
00:13:09.997 --> 00:13:12.458
I think a little screen time
would be just fine.

186
00:13:12.542 --> 00:13:13.793
Help with your grades too.

187
00:13:14.585 --> 00:13:17.505
Okay. now that we
dissected our frogs.

188
00:13:17.588 --> 00:13:20.758
let's go back to the diagram
and compare it with what we saw.

189
00:13:21.926 --> 00:13:23.010
Hey.

190
00:13:23.094 --> 00:13:26.889
Is it true that Amish families
share the same bath water?

191
00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:29.183
'Cause that's weird.

192
00:13:29.267 --> 00:13:31.352
And you're weird.

193
00:13:37.900 --> 00:13:41.404
Notebook. Pencil. Desk.

194
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:42.530
Shoes.

195
00:13:43.614 --> 00:13:44.615
Paper.

196
00:13:46.033 --> 00:13:48.286
Eraser. Calculator.

197
00:13:48.369 --> 00:13:49.495
Everything okay. Charlie?

198
00:13:52.039 --> 00:13:53.457
Yes. Ms. Gardner.

199
00:14:05.178 --> 00:14:06.721
[knocking]

200
00:14:08.306 --> 00:14:09.932
[door opens]

201
00:14:11.767 --> 00:14:12.852
Charlie.

202
00:14:13.895 --> 00:14:15.521
Is everything okay in here?

203
00:14:17.106 --> 00:14:18.566
-[sniffles]
-[door closes]

204
00:14:21.694 --> 00:14:23.529
I don't wanna go to school.

205
00:14:23.613 --> 00:14:25.948
[inhales. exhales]

206
00:14:29.076 --> 00:14:31.120
We just want you
to have a normal life.

207
00:14:31.829 --> 00:14:34.957
I want stupid Wi-Fi.
That's normal.

208
00:14:36.125 --> 00:14:38.127
[crying]

209
00:14:39.086 --> 00:14:40.880
That stuff rots your brains.

210
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:45.676
Do you really believe that?

211
00:14:45.760 --> 00:14:47.261
Mm-hmm.

212
00:14:48.971 --> 00:14:51.015
Plus. it's expensive. you know?

213
00:14:51.724 --> 00:14:54.435
Monthly bills. smartphones.

214
00:14:55.228 --> 00:14:58.689
We just. you know.
we can't afford it right now.

215
00:14:59.649 --> 00:15:00.650
Sorry.

216
00:15:02.652 --> 00:15:04.445
It happened again.

217
00:15:08.324 --> 00:15:09.951
The bad thing.

218
00:15:11.827 --> 00:15:13.162
This boy made fun of me.

219
00:15:15.373 --> 00:15:17.959
[exhales] He called me weird.

220
00:15:18.543 --> 00:15:19.919
You're not weird.

221
00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:22.213
I'm worse.

222
00:15:22.296 --> 00:15:24.465
No. No.

223
00:15:24.966 --> 00:15:26.342
You're special.

224
00:15:29.387 --> 00:15:32.139
I knew it
the day that you were born.

225
00:15:33.808 --> 00:15:37.603
You were warm and toasty.
like a buttery muffin.

226
00:15:45.361 --> 00:15:47.280
Are you scared of me?

227
00:15:47.864 --> 00:15:49.240
Oh.

228
00:15:51.075 --> 00:15:53.452
I could never be scared of you.

229
00:15:55.621 --> 00:15:56.747
Come here.

230
00:15:58.833 --> 00:16:01.502
[inhales. exhales]

231
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:11.345
Three years.
We got-- We got too comfortable.

232
00:16:11.429 --> 00:16:13.306
[Andy] I just don't get it.
Like. why now?

233
00:16:13.890 --> 00:16:16.809
What's the trigger? She's not in puberty.

234
00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:18.477
-[chuckles]
-Is she?

235
00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:20.813
-No.
-Oh. God.

236
00:16:22.565 --> 00:16:24.025
[sighs]

237
00:16:26.527 --> 00:16:28.279
It really scared her when it happened.

238
00:16:28.362 --> 00:16:30.865
-Maybe she needs to be scared.
-She needs to be trained.

239
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:33.743
-Oh. my God.
-Our responsibility is getting her ready.

240
00:16:33.826 --> 00:16:35.703
Making her strong in case they come.

241
00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:38.039
Our responsibility is to protect her.

242
00:16:38.122 --> 00:16:39.540
Training her is protecting her.

243
00:16:39.624 --> 00:16:42.460
Says the one who hates her power so much.
she won't even use it.

244
00:16:42.543 --> 00:16:45.296
We-- It's different for us.
We know what it's like--

245
00:16:45.379 --> 00:16:46.547
Be normal?

246
00:16:47.215 --> 00:16:49.258
But when you're born this way--

247
00:16:49.342 --> 00:16:51.802
She's not a robot. She's a little girl.

248
00:16:51.886 --> 00:16:55.306
With little girl feelings and emotions.
which are wildly unpredictable.

249
00:16:56.015 --> 00:16:57.016
It's too dangerous.

250
00:16:57.099 --> 00:16:59.227
She just has to shove it down
and keep it hidden.

251
00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.811
She did it before.

252
00:17:02.271 --> 00:17:03.773
She can do it again.

253
00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:05.441
[whistle blows]

254
00:17:06.275 --> 00:17:09.194
[students shouting. chattering]

255
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:36.055
[Gavin laughs] Loser.

256
00:17:37.348 --> 00:17:38.391
[chuckles]

257
00:17:39.183 --> 00:17:40.351
Let's go.

258
00:17:41.686 --> 00:17:42.979
[Ms. Gardner] You okay. Charlie?

259
00:17:45.857 --> 00:17:46.858
Weirdo.

260
00:17:52.196 --> 00:17:53.656
Yeah. run away. you freak.

261
00:17:55.324 --> 00:17:56.325
[Ms. Gardner] Charlie?

262
00:18:15.136 --> 00:18:16.137
Charlie?

263
00:18:17.805 --> 00:18:19.807
[water running]

264
00:18:38.409 --> 00:18:39.619
Charlie?

265
00:18:47.710 --> 00:18:48.920
What the…

266
00:18:58.804 --> 00:19:01.015
Please. Charlie?

267
00:19:02.308 --> 00:19:03.851
Whatever's going on…

268
00:19:05.728 --> 00:19:07.271
Charlie? [gasps]

269
00:19:09.023 --> 00:19:11.442
[crying] Please leave.
Please.

270
00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:16.656
Charlie?

271
00:19:20.618 --> 00:19:21.869
[gasps]

272
00:19:21.953 --> 00:19:23.746
[door banging]

273
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.094
[screams]

274
00:19:42.056 --> 00:19:44.058
[whimpering]

275
00:19:56.028 --> 00:19:57.947
Holy shit.

276
00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:11.711
[chattering]

277
00:20:13.963 --> 00:20:16.966
-<i>It won't happen again.
</i>-How can you be so sure?

278
00:20:18.009 --> 00:20:21.554
Does Charlie have a history
of destructive behavior?

279
00:20:21.637 --> 00:20:22.847
No. of course not.

280
00:20:23.514 --> 00:20:26.726
[principal] She's been less than
forthcoming about how she did it.

281
00:20:26.809 --> 00:20:30.563
What she used
to cause the explosion.

282
00:20:30.646 --> 00:20:33.858
Please don't call it an explosion.
It makes her sound like a terrorist.

283
00:20:33.941 --> 00:20:37.528
The bathroom stall exploded. ma'am.
What would you like us to call it?

284
00:20:37.612 --> 00:20:41.949
Regardless. the police want to
investigate the matter further.

285
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:47.455
That blast was like a siren call.

286
00:20:47.538 --> 00:20:49.248
I know you don't wanna hear this.

287
00:20:49.332 --> 00:20:51.626
but none of this would've happened
if she knew how to use it.

288
00:20:52.251 --> 00:20:54.795
Jesus. Look at my eyes.

289
00:20:55.546 --> 00:20:58.174
Every time I try to do it.
i-i-it chips away at me now.

290
00:20:58.257 --> 00:21:01.093
I can't do the push
without my eyes literally bleeding now.

291
00:21:01.802 --> 00:21:02.929
Why didn't you tell me?

292
00:21:03.012 --> 00:21:05.139
[sighs] Come on.

293
00:21:05.223 --> 00:21:06.724
That doesn't mean
it will happen to Charlie.

294
00:21:06.807 --> 00:21:08.184
That's not a risk I'm willing to take.

295
00:21:10.520 --> 00:21:15.399
I don't have your power. Okay?
I can't push her if she loses control.

296
00:21:15.483 --> 00:21:17.443
Well. I would never push my own kid.

297
00:21:19.320 --> 00:21:21.656
Our cover is blown. okay?

298
00:21:21.739 --> 00:21:24.534
If they catch her.
they're gonna lock her away.

299
00:21:24.617 --> 00:21:26.702
They're gonna run tests on her
for the rest of her life.

300
00:21:26.786 --> 00:21:28.996
They're gonna take her.
they're gonna put her in a cage.

301
00:21:29.080 --> 00:21:30.706
We'll never see her again. Vick.

302
00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:32.792
Who knows
what's gonna happen to her?

303
00:21:34.043 --> 00:21:35.795
If who catches me?

304
00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:40.258
You're supposed to be
in your room. Charlie.

305
00:21:40.341 --> 00:21:41.676
You were yelling.

306
00:21:45.388 --> 00:21:48.182
Charlie. I need you to go to your room
right now. and pack a bag.

307
00:21:48.266 --> 00:21:50.685
-We're leaving in the morning.
-Sweetie. do you think…

308
00:21:50.768 --> 00:21:52.687
Are we bad people. Charlie?

309
00:21:53.729 --> 00:21:54.939
Mm-mmm.

310
00:21:55.022 --> 00:21:56.983
[Andy] Do you know why
we have to move all the time?

311
00:21:58.192 --> 00:21:59.402
Mmm?

312
00:21:59.485 --> 00:22:01.320
Because of your work.

313
00:22:01.404 --> 00:22:04.532
But also because bad men are after us.

314
00:22:05.116 --> 00:22:06.367
Really bad.

315
00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:10.204
Because of the special things
that we can do. The pushing and the fire.

316
00:22:10.288 --> 00:22:12.790
And if they catch us.
they're gonna put us in jail.

317
00:22:12.874 --> 00:22:15.459
It's why we can't have cell phones
or Wi-Fi.

318
00:22:15.543 --> 00:22:17.420
Because they can track it.

319
00:22:17.503 --> 00:22:19.589
I'm sorry we lied to you.

320
00:22:20.256 --> 00:22:22.633
But I ran to the bathroom
so I wouldn't hurt anyone.

321
00:22:22.717 --> 00:22:26.053
That was the right thing to do. Charlie.
That was-- That was right.

322
00:22:26.137 --> 00:22:28.598
I tried to throw it in the water.
but it didn't work.

323
00:22:29.140 --> 00:22:32.226
And now we're in trouble and we're
going to jail. and it's all my fault!

324
00:22:32.310 --> 00:22:33.352
Okay. you gotta stay calm.

325
00:22:33.436 --> 00:22:35.021
-Calm down. Charlie.
-Just stay calm. sweetie.

326
00:22:35.104 --> 00:22:37.315
-You're okay.
-I'm not okay. Stop saying that.

327
00:22:37.398 --> 00:22:38.941
And I'm not special.

328
00:22:39.025 --> 00:22:41.360
-I'm a monster!
-You are not a monster.

329
00:22:41.444 --> 00:22:42.570
You need to calm down.

330
00:22:42.653 --> 00:22:44.071
-You're not a monster.
-I'm a monster.

331
00:22:44.155 --> 00:22:45.948
I'm a monster!

332
00:22:46.699 --> 00:22:47.742
Charlie.

333
00:22:47.825 --> 00:22:49.535
I hate living like this!

334
00:22:49.619 --> 00:22:51.495
Tough luck. Charlie.
This is who you are!

335
00:22:51.579 --> 00:22:53.915
Please. Andy. Stop.

336
00:22:53.998 --> 00:22:56.417
You made me this way. [cries]

337
00:22:56.501 --> 00:23:00.213
-Charlie. please!
-I hate who I am. and I hate you!

338
00:23:00.296 --> 00:23:02.006
[screaming] Charlie!

339
00:23:03.758 --> 00:23:05.092
Charlie!

340
00:23:06.594 --> 00:23:08.095
[gasping. panting]

341
00:23:08.179 --> 00:23:09.764
Oh. God. Oh. God.

342
00:23:11.265 --> 00:23:12.475
Jesus Christ.

343
00:23:13.434 --> 00:23:16.979
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

344
00:23:17.063 --> 00:23:20.399
Charlie. Charlie. no. Charlie. no.

345
00:23:20.483 --> 00:23:22.818
-[Andy] Charlie.
-Charlie. no. I'm gonna be okay.

346
00:23:22.902 --> 00:23:24.779
Shh. Shh.

347
00:23:24.862 --> 00:23:26.697
-[Vicky groans]
-She's okay.

348
00:23:26.781 --> 00:23:29.951
-[dispatcher] <i>911. what is your emergency?
</i>-[Andy] See? She's fine.

349
00:23:31.285 --> 00:23:32.745
-Come on. Please.
-<i>Hello?</i>

350
00:23:32.828 --> 00:23:34.539
-[Vicky] I'm okay.
-<i>Hello?</i>

351
00:23:35.665 --> 00:23:36.916
-<i>Are you there?
</i>-[phone beeps]

352
00:23:37.917 --> 00:23:40.670
Okay. It's okay. It's all right.

353
00:23:45.508 --> 00:23:46.884
It's okay. It's all right.

354
00:24:18.207 --> 00:24:20.376
["Control I'm Here" playing]

355
00:24:20.459 --> 00:24:21.460
♪ <i>I'm here</i> ♪

356
00:24:28.968 --> 00:24:32.889
♪ <i>We close our eyes
We close our eyes</i> ♪

357
00:24:32.972 --> 00:24:36.142
♪ <i>Close them in your dreams
Close them in your home</i> ♪

358
00:24:36.225 --> 00:24:37.768
♪ <i>I'm here to stay</i> ♪

359
00:24:37.852 --> 00:24:39.812
♪ <i>They don't go away</i> ♪

360
00:24:40.730 --> 00:24:43.733
♪ <i>You don't need me</i> ♪

361
00:24:43.816 --> 00:24:45.568
♪ <i>I'll slip away</i> ♪

362
00:24:48.404 --> 00:24:50.907
♪ <i>You can't hear me…</i> ♪

363
00:24:50.990 --> 00:24:52.617
[vibrating]

364
00:24:58.331 --> 00:24:59.707
[caller] <i>Is this Rainbird?</i>

365
00:25:00.249 --> 00:25:01.250
Yes.

366
00:25:01.334 --> 00:25:04.045
This is Captain Jane Hollister. DSI.

367
00:25:04.128 --> 00:25:06.297
I'm reactivating you. Rainbird.

368
00:25:09.217 --> 00:25:10.927
If that would be of interest.

369
00:25:11.594 --> 00:25:15.598
Of course it's still the cleaning up
other people's shit. just not literally.

370
00:25:18.267 --> 00:25:20.144
I left that life.

371
00:25:20.228 --> 00:25:22.063
[Hollister] <i>Yeah.
and how's that workin' out for ya?</i>

372
00:25:23.356 --> 00:25:24.398
<i>I know what happened.</i>

373
00:25:24.482 --> 00:25:28.152
The Shop used you up
and threw you out like unwanted trash.

374
00:25:29.153 --> 00:25:30.488
<i>And that wasn't right.</i>

375
00:25:32.323 --> 00:25:34.700
But that was the old guard. I'm the new.

376
00:25:40.081 --> 00:25:43.835
Something's happened. Rainbird.
and I need it handled with discretion.

377
00:25:43.918 --> 00:25:46.128
I understand that was your specialty.

378
00:25:53.094 --> 00:25:54.428
[Rainbird] <i>What is the target?</i>

379
00:25:57.932 --> 00:26:02.603
Something for which
you are uniquely qualified.

380
00:26:04.438 --> 00:26:09.944
But unlike the others.
I need this quarry back alive.

381
00:26:11.445 --> 00:26:13.239
<i>Is that something you can handle?</i>

382
00:26:25.835 --> 00:26:27.837
[crying]

383
00:26:30.464 --> 00:26:32.592
[Andy] Good job. Good job.

384
00:26:34.719 --> 00:26:36.220
Ooh.

385
00:26:38.639 --> 00:26:39.849
There we go.

386
00:26:40.808 --> 00:26:41.809
You okay?

387
00:26:41.893 --> 00:26:43.603
Ow. ow. ow.

388
00:26:43.686 --> 00:26:44.687
A little more.

389
00:26:45.688 --> 00:26:47.648
[exhales]

390
00:26:47.732 --> 00:26:49.525
Vick. this is bad.

391
00:26:52.778 --> 00:26:54.280
Ah. fuck.

392
00:26:54.363 --> 00:26:55.489
Almost done.

393
00:26:57.533 --> 00:26:58.868
[exhales]

394
00:27:00.161 --> 00:27:01.787
That's it.

395
00:27:01.871 --> 00:27:03.873
You could've pushed her.

396
00:27:03.956 --> 00:27:07.835
We have no idea what's happening
when I'm going into those people's minds.

397
00:27:07.919 --> 00:27:08.920
moving things around.

398
00:27:09.003 --> 00:27:10.505
Why would you want me to do that
to Charlie?

399
00:27:10.588 --> 00:27:12.924
-What if I mess her up?
-And if she kills one of us?

400
00:27:13.007 --> 00:27:14.926
Don't fucking go there.

401
00:27:15.009 --> 00:27:16.427
-Andy.
-Oh.

402
00:27:16.511 --> 00:27:18.971
This is what happens
when you stuff it down.

403
00:27:19.889 --> 00:27:21.307
[whispers] It doesn't go away.

404
00:27:23.309 --> 00:27:25.353
Can you take her to the movies
or something? Please?

405
00:27:25.436 --> 00:27:27.021
Ice cream or something?

406
00:27:30.483 --> 00:27:32.944
[moans. whimpers]

407
00:27:33.027 --> 00:27:34.862
-Just get some rest. okay?
-Okay.

408
00:27:54.882 --> 00:27:58.010
[gasping. sniffling]

409
00:27:59.762 --> 00:28:01.389
[gasps]

410
00:29:07.163 --> 00:29:09.749
-[knocking]
-[gasping. panting]

411
00:29:24.096 --> 00:29:25.097
Vicky McGee?

412
00:29:25.723 --> 00:29:29.393
I'm just following up on an emergency call
from earlier tonight.

413
00:29:29.477 --> 00:29:32.104
Oh. Yeah. It was a grease fire.

414
00:29:32.730 --> 00:29:35.358
On the stove.
My daughter overreacted.

415
00:29:35.441 --> 00:29:37.568
If you or your daughter need help…

416
00:29:37.652 --> 00:29:39.028
It's nothing like that.

417
00:29:40.863 --> 00:29:41.864
Honestly.

418
00:29:44.951 --> 00:29:48.162
If you're sure about that.
you have a good night. then.

419
00:30:04.136 --> 00:30:06.430
Oh. Charlie.

420
00:30:06.514 --> 00:30:08.266
[groans]

421
00:30:21.737 --> 00:30:23.197
Where did they go?

422
00:30:24.282 --> 00:30:27.285
Your husband and the girl.

423
00:30:30.580 --> 00:30:31.581
[groans]

424
00:30:32.498 --> 00:30:36.252
[Vicky's voice] <i>Ice cream. Movies.</i>

425
00:30:39.213 --> 00:30:43.259
Ice cream… or the movies?

426
00:30:44.010 --> 00:30:45.553
[gasps]

427
00:30:48.097 --> 00:30:50.057
Did you think you were unique?

428
00:30:50.141 --> 00:30:53.811
Before they tested their poison
on pretty. young coeds.

429
00:30:53.895 --> 00:30:55.855
they had to use the lab rats.

430
00:31:04.363 --> 00:31:05.990
And you're out of practice.

431
00:31:14.957 --> 00:31:16.209
[panting]

432
00:31:35.728 --> 00:31:37.104
[lock clicks]

433
00:31:38.856 --> 00:31:40.149
Ow.

434
00:31:46.197 --> 00:31:47.823
How could you work for them?

435
00:31:47.907 --> 00:31:49.951
Help them after what they did to you?

436
00:31:50.034 --> 00:31:53.079
Come peacefully. and you'll live.

437
00:31:53.162 --> 00:31:55.498
I will die before I let them have her.

438
00:31:55.581 --> 00:31:58.751
Your life to them is a secondary concern.

439
00:31:58.835 --> 00:31:59.961
And yours?

440
00:32:03.130 --> 00:32:04.465
[screams]

441
00:32:08.302 --> 00:32:10.555
[screams]

442
00:32:10.638 --> 00:32:12.557
[panting]

443
00:32:24.861 --> 00:32:28.531
When you see her.
you'll understand.

444
00:32:28.614 --> 00:32:29.907
And you will regret.

445
00:32:41.669 --> 00:32:44.130
Do you think she'll forgive me?

446
00:32:47.508 --> 00:32:49.218
Well. she's your mom.

447
00:32:49.302 --> 00:32:50.845
She'll always forgive you.

448
00:32:52.096 --> 00:32:53.181
No matter what.

449
00:32:56.893 --> 00:32:59.020
[whispers] It was supposed to be you.

450
00:32:59.103 --> 00:33:00.104
What?

451
00:33:05.610 --> 00:33:07.737
It was supposed to be you.

452
00:33:09.697 --> 00:33:10.990
[sighs]

453
00:33:21.626 --> 00:33:22.627
[Andy sighs]

454
00:33:26.005 --> 00:33:27.131
I feel weird.

455
00:33:28.508 --> 00:33:29.967
Too much Rocky Road.

456
00:33:31.844 --> 00:33:33.638
She's probably asleep.
I'm gonna check on her. okay?

457
00:33:33.721 --> 00:33:37.225
Here. take that to the trash.
And then throw on your pj's. all right?

458
00:33:55.660 --> 00:33:57.662
[breathes heavily]

459
00:33:57.745 --> 00:33:58.913
Surrender.

460
00:33:58.996 --> 00:34:00.665
-[Andy] Charlie?
-Daddy.

461
00:34:00.748 --> 00:34:01.999
No one gets hurt.

462
00:34:03.876 --> 00:34:05.086
[neck cracks]

463
00:34:06.879 --> 00:34:08.089
Let her go.

464
00:34:09.882 --> 00:34:11.509
You know what it costs. don't you?

465
00:34:12.885 --> 00:34:14.136
To hurt someone.

466
00:34:14.219 --> 00:34:16.138
To take a life.

467
00:34:16.222 --> 00:34:18.431
Would you ask that of your own child?

468
00:34:22.061 --> 00:34:23.062
[Andy] Do you feel that?

469
00:34:23.938 --> 00:34:25.898
Let her go. or it's gonna get a lot worse.

470
00:34:26.482 --> 00:34:27.567
Where's Mommy?

471
00:34:27.650 --> 00:34:30.695
She has no aim without sight
if she's like the rest of us.

472
00:34:30.777 --> 00:34:32.237
Where's my wife?

473
00:34:37.409 --> 00:34:38.578
[Charlie] Where's Mommy?

474
00:34:41.496 --> 00:34:43.373
I don't know. sweetheart.

475
00:34:43.456 --> 00:34:45.001
Yes. you do.

476
00:34:45.083 --> 00:34:47.043
Where's Mommy? Tell me now!

477
00:34:49.589 --> 00:34:51.507
-[gasps]
-Mom?

478
00:34:51.591 --> 00:34:52.967
-[panting]
-[shouts]

479
00:34:58.598 --> 00:35:01.058
[screams]

480
00:35:03.895 --> 00:35:05.605
Run. Run. Charlie!

481
00:35:06.480 --> 00:35:08.399
[smoke alarm blaring]

482
00:35:08.482 --> 00:35:09.775
-Run!
-Mommy!

483
00:35:16.699 --> 00:35:18.159
[coughs]

484
00:35:26.584 --> 00:35:28.836
-Come on. We have to get somewhere safe.
-[crying]

485
00:35:47.563 --> 00:35:48.814
[knocking]

486
00:35:48.898 --> 00:35:51.651
[employee] Doctor Wanless.
you have a guest.

487
00:35:54.195 --> 00:35:55.696
Good morning. Joseph.

488
00:35:56.864 --> 00:35:58.449
I brought you something.

489
00:36:00.576 --> 00:36:02.453
Your favorite colors too.

490
00:36:09.585 --> 00:36:12.672
I'm Captain Hollister.
newly appointed. DSI.

491
00:36:12.755 --> 00:36:16.425
Why are you here? Mmm?

492
00:36:16.509 --> 00:36:17.718
Captain?

493
00:36:17.802 --> 00:36:20.888
I made calls to your predecessor.

494
00:36:20.972 --> 00:36:22.682
They went unanswered.

495
00:36:22.765 --> 00:36:23.933
[scoffs]

496
00:36:24.016 --> 00:36:25.601
But now.

497
00:36:25.685 --> 00:36:30.940
they stuff a new face
into the same old suit.

498
00:36:31.023 --> 00:36:33.860
and that face just comes…

499
00:36:34.986 --> 00:36:36.404
knocking on my door!

500
00:36:36.487 --> 00:36:38.030
With all due respect. Doctor.

501
00:36:38.114 --> 00:36:41.242
Captain McConnell doesn't have
the legs for this outfit.

502
00:36:41.325 --> 00:36:43.452
Completely oblivious

503
00:36:43.536 --> 00:36:47.582
to the dire nature
of the situation we've created.

504
00:36:47.665 --> 00:36:48.749
We found them.

505
00:36:49.542 --> 00:36:50.793
Joseph…

506
00:36:52.503 --> 00:36:53.963
shall we talk?

507
00:37:02.305 --> 00:37:03.723
[Vicky] <i>When you see her.</i>

508
00:37:04.473 --> 00:37:06.017
<i>you'll understand.</i>

509
00:37:06.100 --> 00:37:07.560
<i>And you will regret.</i>

510
00:37:20.740 --> 00:37:22.992
I miss you. Mom. I'll get him.

511
00:37:45.640 --> 00:37:48.267
[exhales] Let's see.

512
00:38:21.717 --> 00:38:22.844
[Vicky chuckles]

513
00:38:22.927 --> 00:38:25.638
[screaming. chuckling. gasping]

514
00:38:43.114 --> 00:38:45.032
[chuckles] Yeah.

515
00:38:45.116 --> 00:38:47.952
Oh. Hi! Hi. kitty. kitty.

516
00:38:49.370 --> 00:38:50.746
-Hi.
-[cat meows]

517
00:38:51.414 --> 00:38:52.874
Come here. kitty. kitty.

518
00:38:53.457 --> 00:38:54.625
Come here. It's okay.

519
00:38:55.376 --> 00:38:56.836
Don't run away. Come on.

520
00:38:57.503 --> 00:38:59.422
It's okay. I'm nice.

521
00:38:59.505 --> 00:39:00.548
I won't hurt you.

522
00:39:01.132 --> 00:39:02.133
[snarls]

523
00:39:02.216 --> 00:39:04.468
-Ah.
-[cat hisses]

524
00:39:04.552 --> 00:39:05.636
[yowls]

525
00:39:06.637 --> 00:39:07.847
Charlie?

526
00:39:10.808 --> 00:39:11.893
Charlie?

527
00:39:15.479 --> 00:39:16.981
[cat groans]

528
00:39:17.064 --> 00:39:18.608
He scratched me.

529
00:39:20.776 --> 00:39:22.236
[groaning]

530
00:39:23.529 --> 00:39:25.281
Honey. he's in pain.

531
00:39:26.490 --> 00:39:28.367
You have to put him
out of his misery. all right?

532
00:39:28.451 --> 00:39:31.787
[crying] I really didn't mean to.

533
00:39:31.871 --> 00:39:33.956
I know you didn't. I know.

534
00:39:35.041 --> 00:39:36.876
This is what it costs. though.

535
00:39:40.505 --> 00:39:42.340
'Cause it can't be a reaction like that.

536
00:39:42.423 --> 00:39:43.674
It's gotta be…

537
00:39:44.842 --> 00:39:45.843
a decision.

538
00:39:46.719 --> 00:39:48.179
That's the only way you can control it.

539
00:39:49.347 --> 00:39:50.515
You can do it.

540
00:39:52.683 --> 00:39:54.685
[yowls]

541
00:40:03.194 --> 00:40:04.529
[cat shrieks]

542
00:40:09.825 --> 00:40:11.661
[sobbing]

543
00:40:11.744 --> 00:40:12.995
Good job.

544
00:40:18.668 --> 00:40:20.419
I want to help her.

545
00:40:20.503 --> 00:40:22.171
You want to use her.

546
00:40:22.255 --> 00:40:24.257
The girl. she can't help what she is.

547
00:40:24.340 --> 00:40:28.302
The poor thing. she's been
brain-fucked from birth.

548
00:40:28.386 --> 00:40:32.390
This is a chance
to turn a past failure

549
00:40:32.473 --> 00:40:34.267
into present success.

550
00:40:34.350 --> 00:40:36.435
I want you to come back to work.

551
00:40:36.978 --> 00:40:38.229
Doctor Wanless.

552
00:40:38.312 --> 00:40:40.022
[sighs]

553
00:40:41.065 --> 00:40:44.735
How hard must it have been for them?

554
00:40:45.319 --> 00:40:47.780
The parents.
when the girl was born?

555
00:40:47.864 --> 00:40:49.824
The bottle is late.

556
00:40:50.491 --> 00:40:52.410
The baby cries.

557
00:40:52.493 --> 00:40:55.329
And a teddy bear

558
00:40:55.413 --> 00:40:57.665
bursts into flames.

559
00:40:58.791 --> 00:41:00.293
Right there.

560
00:41:01.002 --> 00:41:03.462
In the crib. beside her.

561
00:41:04.088 --> 00:41:07.341
Can you imagine their fear?

562
00:41:08.593 --> 00:41:11.387
And it's awful. that's really…
What's your point?

563
00:41:12.346 --> 00:41:16.350
The girl's power is in its infancy.

564
00:41:18.144 --> 00:41:19.604
Terrible. yes.

565
00:41:20.771 --> 00:41:23.816
but trivial compared to what's coming.

566
00:41:24.775 --> 00:41:27.445
But she's growing.

567
00:41:27.528 --> 00:41:29.530
our little girl.

568
00:41:29.614 --> 00:41:33.659
She is becoming a young woman.

569
00:41:33.743 --> 00:41:36.078
And someday soon.

570
00:41:36.162 --> 00:41:38.539
the power will grow too.

571
00:41:38.623 --> 00:41:40.249
Perhaps it already has.

572
00:41:42.376 --> 00:41:45.421
And then. one day.

573
00:41:45.505 --> 00:41:47.507
she may be capable…

574
00:41:49.759 --> 00:41:54.138
of creating a nuclear explosion

575
00:41:54.222 --> 00:41:57.850
simply with the force of her mind.

576
00:41:57.934 --> 00:42:03.314
Doctor. we built a facility
especially for people like Charlie.

577
00:42:03.397 --> 00:42:05.233
We can teach her.

578
00:42:05.316 --> 00:42:06.692
We can train her.

579
00:42:06.776 --> 00:42:08.736
You can exploit her.

580
00:42:08.819 --> 00:42:10.905
Don't you lecture me
on morality.

581
00:42:10.988 --> 00:42:14.242
You developed Lot Six.
You gave it to those kids.

582
00:42:14.325 --> 00:42:15.409
And it was a mistake!

583
00:42:15.493 --> 00:42:17.620
Well. that's too fuckin' bad!

584
00:42:18.120 --> 00:42:20.456
-It's done!
-[sighs]

585
00:42:20.540 --> 00:42:23.209
Jesus fuck--
We're not gonna clone her.

586
00:42:23.292 --> 00:42:25.878
We're not gonna make
a little army of Charlies.

587
00:42:25.962 --> 00:42:27.296
We just-- We…

588
00:42:29.215 --> 00:42:31.217
We want to understand her.

589
00:42:34.595 --> 00:42:36.222
She's the first of her kind.

590
00:42:36.848 --> 00:42:39.976
And no one understands her
better than you.

591
00:42:40.059 --> 00:42:42.353
The man who made the serum.

592
00:42:42.436 --> 00:42:46.274
You're the father of it all.

593
00:42:46.858 --> 00:42:48.401
What do you say?

594
00:42:54.782 --> 00:42:59.579
There are none so blind
as those who will not see.

595
00:43:02.582 --> 00:43:03.583
What?

596
00:43:06.711 --> 00:43:08.296
Heed my words…

597
00:43:09.589 --> 00:43:10.882
very carefully.

598
00:43:13.593 --> 00:43:15.011
Terminate the girl.

599
00:43:15.970 --> 00:43:18.973
Or one day.
she will destroy us all.

600
00:43:19.056 --> 00:43:20.516
Do you hear me?

601
00:43:22.310 --> 00:43:24.270
Terminate her.

602
00:43:26.272 --> 00:43:28.900
I hoped this would've gone better.

603
00:43:34.155 --> 00:43:35.156
That's good.

604
00:43:36.407 --> 00:43:37.491
Can we pray?

605
00:43:40.036 --> 00:43:41.913
Yeah. Sure. we can pray.

606
00:43:43.080 --> 00:43:44.624
[exhales] All right.

607
00:43:48.252 --> 00:43:49.462
Dear God…

608
00:43:50.963 --> 00:43:52.256
please let this…

609
00:43:53.132 --> 00:43:55.801
cat be happy…

610
00:43:55.885 --> 00:43:57.553
in cat heaven.

611
00:43:57.637 --> 00:44:02.016
And. um. just. you know.
make sure that-- that he. uh…

612
00:44:02.975 --> 00:44:04.268
or she…

613
00:44:06.062 --> 00:44:07.188
or they…

614
00:44:07.271 --> 00:44:10.274
It's like a big cat party
in cat heaven.

615
00:44:11.192 --> 00:44:12.693
And bless Mommy too.

616
00:44:17.240 --> 00:44:19.700
Yeah. and bless Mommy too.

617
00:44:25.248 --> 00:44:28.167
You know what Mom wanted you to learn
more than anything in the world?

618
00:44:32.004 --> 00:44:34.465
She wanted you to learn
how to use your power.

619
00:44:35.842 --> 00:44:37.343
Because it's incredible.

620
00:44:37.426 --> 00:44:39.387
And I bet if you have her powers. you--

621
00:44:40.972 --> 00:44:42.765
you probably have mine too.

622
00:44:45.142 --> 00:44:47.019
-The push?
-Yep.

623
00:44:51.941 --> 00:44:53.776
It's serious stuff. Charlie.

624
00:44:54.986 --> 00:44:56.737
That's why Mom wanted to teach you.

625
00:44:56.821 --> 00:44:59.657
To help you understand how to use it.

626
00:45:01.325 --> 00:45:02.910
[sighs]

627
00:45:02.994 --> 00:45:05.371
If you do it too much.
it'll really hurt you.

628
00:45:05.454 --> 00:45:08.040
But I don't feel the heat when it happens.

629
00:45:10.543 --> 00:45:12.461
It hurts you on the inside. I mean.

630
00:45:14.505 --> 00:45:15.715
Actually.

631
00:45:16.883 --> 00:45:18.467
it feels kinda good.

632
00:45:26.976 --> 00:45:29.353
Why can't we drive our own car?

633
00:45:29.437 --> 00:45:30.938
Because they're looking for us.

634
00:45:33.774 --> 00:45:35.484
They won't really put us in jail.

635
00:45:35.568 --> 00:45:36.903
Not you.

636
00:45:39.113 --> 00:45:40.198
They'll study you.

637
00:45:41.991 --> 00:45:43.284
Like the frog.

638
00:45:44.452 --> 00:45:45.494
Yeah.

639
00:45:47.121 --> 00:45:48.414
Yeah. like the frog.

640
00:45:48.497 --> 00:45:50.082
[vehicle approaching]

641
00:45:50.166 --> 00:45:51.751
Here's one.

642
00:45:51.834 --> 00:45:53.669
Oh. come on. please. Yes!

643
00:45:55.671 --> 00:45:56.672
Okay.

644
00:45:58.382 --> 00:46:00.343
Do you really think this is safe?

645
00:46:01.093 --> 00:46:03.054
Right now. I think
we have to get off this road.

646
00:46:03.137 --> 00:46:04.138
So…

647
00:46:05.097 --> 00:46:06.974
Come on. We'll be smart.

648
00:46:08.726 --> 00:46:09.852
Be clever. Let's go.

649
00:46:11.521 --> 00:46:14.565
Oh. man. I didn't think anyone
was gonna stop. [chuckles]

650
00:46:14.649 --> 00:46:17.527
There's a lotta weirdos
around these parts. [chuckles]

651
00:46:17.610 --> 00:46:18.653
You one of 'em?

652
00:46:18.736 --> 00:46:21.155
No. no. no. We're very normal.

653
00:46:21.239 --> 00:46:22.698
Tell the nice man your name.
sweetheart.

654
00:46:22.782 --> 00:46:25.034
I'm Roberta.
but they call me Bobbi.

655
00:46:25.576 --> 00:46:29.247
[Andy] Yeah. we're headed up to Boston.
My car broke down a ways back.

656
00:46:29.330 --> 00:46:32.041
-Boston is a hell of a walk from here.
-Yeah. I know.

657
00:46:32.124 --> 00:46:34.627
We really gotta get there.
Is there any chance you can take us?

658
00:46:34.710 --> 00:46:36.379
To Boston?

659
00:46:36.462 --> 00:46:37.755
I'll cover your gas.

660
00:46:38.673 --> 00:46:42.468
I got things to do.
I gotta check up on my wife.

661
00:46:42.552 --> 00:46:43.678
What about 100 bucks?

662
00:46:47.014 --> 00:46:48.432
[neck cracks]

663
00:46:54.397 --> 00:46:55.398
100 bucks.

664
00:47:00.152 --> 00:47:03.030
{\an8}Well. I'm not above a Benjamin.

665
00:47:04.824 --> 00:47:05.867
Climb in.

666
00:47:07.660 --> 00:47:09.203
Hey. it's lunchtime.

667
00:47:09.287 --> 00:47:12.331
The wife and I usually put out
a little sandwich spread about now.

668
00:47:12.415 --> 00:47:15.042
Why don't you come to the house
and fuel up for a bit?

669
00:47:15.793 --> 00:47:17.712
I don't know. we've…

670
00:47:17.795 --> 00:47:18.796
My wife's waiting.

671
00:47:22.508 --> 00:47:23.843
But Bobbi needs to eat.

672
00:47:26.929 --> 00:47:27.930
Comin' up.

673
00:48:05.885 --> 00:48:07.970
[exhales] Come on in.

674
00:48:08.846 --> 00:48:11.098
Let's get some food in your bellies.

675
00:48:11.182 --> 00:48:13.559
Would it be okay
if I played with your chickens?

676
00:48:13.643 --> 00:48:16.145
Just watch out for the turds. [chuckles]

677
00:48:17.897 --> 00:48:20.566
-Yeah. sure. Stay close. all right?
-Yep.

678
00:48:21.442 --> 00:48:23.486
Try not to cook any of them.

679
00:48:23.569 --> 00:48:26.239
[clucking]

680
00:48:36.916 --> 00:48:38.709
[voice whispers]

681
00:48:41.546 --> 00:48:43.881
Essi! We're home.

682
00:48:44.841 --> 00:48:46.968
Got some guests
for supper. Essi.

683
00:48:47.051 --> 00:48:48.719
Little Bobbi and her dad…

684
00:48:48.803 --> 00:48:51.556
-I don't think I caught your name.
-Frank.

685
00:48:52.765 --> 00:48:54.308
Bobbi and Frank.

686
00:48:54.809 --> 00:48:57.353
[fridge door opens. closes]

687
00:48:57.436 --> 00:48:58.479
Cold beer?

688
00:48:59.355 --> 00:49:01.941
Yeah. sure. Why not? [chuckles]

689
00:49:02.024 --> 00:49:03.025
Thank you.

690
00:49:03.985 --> 00:49:07.363
So. what do you do. Frank?

691
00:49:07.446 --> 00:49:09.240
To keep the lights on?

692
00:49:09.323 --> 00:49:11.742
-I'm a life coach.
-No shit?

693
00:49:11.826 --> 00:49:13.744
Like Tony Robbins on TV?

694
00:49:13.828 --> 00:49:16.539
-No. No. not really like that. but…
-[both laugh]

695
00:49:16.622 --> 00:49:19.542
I saw that documentary
on Netflix.

696
00:49:20.418 --> 00:49:25.131
Ol' Tony cusses like a son of a bitch.
but folks seem to like him.

697
00:49:25.214 --> 00:49:29.010
People will give you their life savings
just to tell 'em they're special.

698
00:49:29.093 --> 00:49:30.344
-Life coach?
-Yeah.

699
00:49:30.428 --> 00:49:32.430
Man! [laughs]

700
00:49:32.513 --> 00:49:34.223
The whole world's gone to hell.

701
00:49:42.023 --> 00:49:45.401
[voice whispering. faint]

702
00:49:50.990 --> 00:49:51.991
Hello?

703
00:49:54.619 --> 00:49:56.078
Is anyone in there?

704
00:50:27.985 --> 00:50:28.986
[gasps]

705
00:50:33.699 --> 00:50:35.701
[machine whirring]

706
00:50:46.462 --> 00:50:47.547
What's your name?

707
00:50:48.756 --> 00:50:49.841
[voice] <i>Essi.</i>

708
00:50:51.759 --> 00:50:52.927
Hi. Essi.

709
00:50:55.054 --> 00:50:56.347
I'm Charlie.

710
00:50:57.265 --> 00:50:58.891
I'm here with my dad.

711
00:51:03.729 --> 00:51:04.856
Hey!

712
00:51:06.524 --> 00:51:07.692
How did you…

713
00:51:08.192 --> 00:51:10.444
Don't go disturbin' Essi.
She needs quiet!

714
00:51:10.528 --> 00:51:11.863
Hey. we're really sorry.

715
00:51:12.572 --> 00:51:13.865
You've been more than kind.

716
00:51:15.241 --> 00:51:16.284
Come on.

717
00:51:17.076 --> 00:51:18.494
We should probably get going.

718
00:51:18.578 --> 00:51:20.246
Where you headed?

719
00:51:20.830 --> 00:51:22.623
And how you gettin' there?

720
00:51:24.166 --> 00:51:25.293
I don't know.

721
00:51:29.130 --> 00:51:32.675
Hey. look. I-- I overreact sometimes.

722
00:51:33.426 --> 00:51:35.344
Especially with the missus.

723
00:51:36.846 --> 00:51:38.097
I apologize.

724
00:51:39.932 --> 00:51:41.726
Oh. how rude of me.

725
00:51:41.809 --> 00:51:42.810
Come on.

726
00:51:50.067 --> 00:51:52.904
Essi. this is Frank.

727
00:51:52.987 --> 00:51:55.406
And I guess you already met Roberta.

728
00:51:56.532 --> 00:52:01.829
She was makin' a left turn out on Route 14
and some a-hole ran a light.

729
00:52:01.913 --> 00:52:03.414
She never saw it coming.

730
00:52:03.497 --> 00:52:04.707
I'm so sorry.

731
00:52:06.167 --> 00:52:08.085
We lost our boy that day too.

732
00:52:10.963 --> 00:52:15.968
But Essi's still alive.
and for that. I'm more than grateful.

733
00:52:20.056 --> 00:52:21.891
You can stay here till you go.

734
00:52:21.974 --> 00:52:24.018
We'd enjoy the company.

735
00:52:30.983 --> 00:52:32.985
Will they find us?

736
00:52:33.069 --> 00:52:35.071
You let me worry
about that.

737
00:52:35.696 --> 00:52:38.824
The most important thing we can do
is just keep running.

738
00:52:38.908 --> 00:52:41.077
If they do. I can hurt them.

739
00:52:44.497 --> 00:52:46.874
[exhales]

740
00:52:46.958 --> 00:52:49.627
I'll only hurt bad people. I promise.

741
00:52:51.546 --> 00:52:53.422
The day you were born.

742
00:52:53.506 --> 00:52:55.091
Do you remember that story?

743
00:52:57.093 --> 00:52:59.095
Mommy said I was a buttery muffin.

744
00:52:59.178 --> 00:53:00.888
Oh. my gosh. You were.

745
00:53:01.472 --> 00:53:03.891
You were just a little buttery muffin.

746
00:53:06.561 --> 00:53:08.145
There's more to that story.

747
00:53:08.855 --> 00:53:11.732
It was so cute how warm you were.

748
00:53:12.441 --> 00:53:15.069
But pretty soon.
your body temperature just went…

749
00:53:15.152 --> 00:53:18.114
[blows] It shot off the charts.

750
00:53:18.197 --> 00:53:21.117
And the doctors. they were all--
they were all confused.

751
00:53:21.200 --> 00:53:22.535
They were…

752
00:53:23.411 --> 00:53:25.913
They didn't know what could cause this.

753
00:53:25.997 --> 00:53:27.915
So. we stayed up
with you all night.

754
00:53:27.999 --> 00:53:29.625
All day.

755
00:53:30.209 --> 00:53:31.711
I could barely keep my eyes open.

756
00:53:31.794 --> 00:53:33.880
I was fallin' asleep everywhere.

757
00:53:33.963 --> 00:53:35.464
[chuckles]

758
00:53:39.844 --> 00:53:42.054
And that's when they took you.

759
00:53:43.723 --> 00:53:45.641
I used to get these premonitions.

760
00:53:45.725 --> 00:53:47.768
This really weird. weird feeling.

761
00:53:47.852 --> 00:53:50.438
Like how I did at the house?

762
00:53:50.521 --> 00:53:51.564
Mm-hmm.

763
00:53:52.315 --> 00:53:53.858
I could sense…

764
00:53:55.067 --> 00:53:57.445
where you were. I could see you.

765
00:53:58.029 --> 00:53:59.488
And I found you.

766
00:53:59.572 --> 00:54:00.865
What did you do?

767
00:54:11.083 --> 00:54:12.084
[cooing]

768
00:54:13.836 --> 00:54:15.129
[neck cracks]

769
00:54:16.422 --> 00:54:20.218
I was so angry at what they had done.

770
00:54:20.885 --> 00:54:22.345
I snapped.

771
00:54:25.306 --> 00:54:27.308
When your partner comes back.

772
00:54:27.391 --> 00:54:29.268
you're gonna shoot him in the chest.

773
00:54:29.936 --> 00:54:31.979
And then you're gonna forget
how to breathe.

774
00:54:34.440 --> 00:54:36.025
And I hurt those men.

775
00:54:38.778 --> 00:54:39.820
[screams]

776
00:54:41.447 --> 00:54:42.448
[gasps]

777
00:54:47.828 --> 00:54:51.290
And those guys. they probably had wives.

778
00:54:52.500 --> 00:54:53.543
Kids

779
00:54:55.169 --> 00:54:56.587
that they loved.

780
00:54:57.171 --> 00:54:59.006
Just like I love you.

781
00:55:00.007 --> 00:55:03.427
And I do. Charlie.
I love you so much.

782
00:55:03.511 --> 00:55:05.555
But when you hurt people.

783
00:55:07.014 --> 00:55:08.891
you don't just hurt them.

784
00:55:08.975 --> 00:55:11.060
It hurts everyone around 'em.

785
00:55:12.436 --> 00:55:14.605
You don't come back from that.

786
00:55:17.024 --> 00:55:18.442
Not ever.

787
00:55:22.446 --> 00:55:27.076
Okay. promise me that you'll never
use your gifts to hurt people.

788
00:55:27.159 --> 00:55:28.244
Promise?

789
00:55:29.620 --> 00:55:30.621
Promise.

790
00:55:35.084 --> 00:55:36.460
Now. sleep.

791
00:55:36.544 --> 00:55:38.379
Get some sleep. all right?

792
00:55:40.089 --> 00:55:41.174
Come here.

793
00:55:42.258 --> 00:55:43.301
Love you.

794
00:55:43.384 --> 00:55:44.552
Love you.

795
00:56:09.785 --> 00:56:11.662
[reporter chattering on TV]

796
00:56:15.416 --> 00:56:18.461
<i>Authorities say
35-year-old Aaron Jeffery Cooper</i>

797
00:56:18.544 --> 00:56:21.339
<i>is operating under the alias "Andy McGee."</i>

798
00:56:21.422 --> 00:56:23.341
<i>He has been wanted
ever since being linked</i>

799
00:56:23.424 --> 00:56:26.427
<i>to the killing
of two federal agents in 2013.</i>

800
00:56:26.511 --> 00:56:30.097
<i>Police say he had been living in Lewiston
with his wife and daughter.</i>

801
00:56:30.181 --> 00:56:33.059
<i>and ask the public
if they come in contact with Cooper.</i>

802
00:56:33.142 --> 00:56:35.394
<i>to contact the police immediately.</i>

803
00:56:35.478 --> 00:56:39.524
<i>We'll have the full details on this story
and more on our next news update.</i>

804
00:56:40.733 --> 00:56:43.778
[news broadcast rewinds]

805
00:56:43.861 --> 00:56:46.113
<i>Police are on the lookout
for a Massachusetts fugitive</i>

806
00:56:46.197 --> 00:56:50.826
<i>now suspected of killing his wife
and kidnapping their 11-year-old daughter.</i>

807
00:56:50.910 --> 00:56:53.913
<i>Authorities say
35-year-old Aaron Jeffery Cooper</i>

808
00:56:53.996 --> 00:56:56.624
<i>is operating under the alias "Andy McGee."</i>

809
00:56:56.707 --> 00:56:58.626
<i>He has been wanted
ever since being linked</i>

810
00:56:58.709 --> 00:57:01.963
<i>to the killing
of two federal agents in 2013.</i>

811
00:57:02.046 --> 00:57:05.591
<i>Police say he had been living in Lewiston
with his wife and daughter.</i>

812
00:57:05.675 --> 00:57:08.761
<i>and asked the public
if they come in contact with Cooper.</i>

813
00:57:08.845 --> 00:57:10.137
<i>to contact the police…</i>

814
00:57:10.221 --> 00:57:11.806
[news broadcast rewinds]

815
00:57:11.889 --> 00:57:13.349
Hey. Irv.

816
00:57:13.432 --> 00:57:14.433
It's not true.

817
00:57:15.935 --> 00:57:17.270
I didn't kill my wife.

818
00:57:19.105 --> 00:57:21.232
You know I didn't kidnap
my daughter either.

819
00:57:21.315 --> 00:57:23.067
I don't know shit.

820
00:57:27.613 --> 00:57:28.781
You been up all night. Irv?

821
00:57:28.865 --> 00:57:34.871
Coming in my house.
eatin' my food. drink my beer.

822
00:57:34.954 --> 00:57:38.040
and all the time.
you a goddamn wife killer!

823
00:57:38.124 --> 00:57:39.125
I didn't kill her.

824
00:57:39.208 --> 00:57:42.128
Does my daughter seem upset with me
in any way? Does she seem scared of me?

825
00:57:42.211 --> 00:57:45.298
I'm trying to protect her.
I'm trying to protect her from them.

826
00:57:45.381 --> 00:57:48.593
You telling me I can't trust the TV?

827
00:57:48.676 --> 00:57:50.094
Shocker. I know.

828
00:57:51.554 --> 00:57:52.763
[grunts]

829
00:57:54.473 --> 00:57:55.683
[groans]

830
00:57:57.810 --> 00:57:59.437
Irv. come on. man.

831
00:58:03.357 --> 00:58:04.859
I know what happened.

832
00:58:06.027 --> 00:58:07.278
What are you talkin' about?

833
00:58:07.361 --> 00:58:09.780
You were driving that day.
and you were arguing.

834
00:58:09.864 --> 00:58:12.283
It got out of control.
and you hit a car head-on.

835
00:58:14.493 --> 00:58:15.870
That's how she got hurt.

836
00:58:16.621 --> 00:58:18.289
That's how Justin died.

837
00:58:19.290 --> 00:58:20.416
Essi told me.

838
00:58:21.834 --> 00:58:22.960
"Told" you?

839
00:58:23.669 --> 00:58:25.087
[Andy] That's why they're after us.

840
00:58:28.090 --> 00:58:29.884
But there's something else.

841
00:58:30.760 --> 00:58:33.930
Something she's been wanting
to tell you for 30 years.

842
00:58:37.058 --> 00:58:38.643
She forgives you.

843
00:58:39.435 --> 00:58:41.729
You've hated yourself all this time.

844
00:58:41.812 --> 00:58:43.981
But it was an accident.

845
00:58:47.610 --> 00:58:49.028
And she forgives you.

846
00:58:50.029 --> 00:58:51.405
[sobs]

847
00:58:54.700 --> 00:58:56.077
[vehicles approaching]

848
00:58:57.203 --> 00:58:58.204
What is that?

849
00:58:59.205 --> 00:59:00.289
I called them.

850
00:59:01.040 --> 00:59:02.083
The police.

851
00:59:02.166 --> 00:59:04.585
When I saw the news.

852
00:59:04.669 --> 00:59:06.504
Oh. my God.

853
00:59:06.587 --> 00:59:10.216
Like I said. I overreact sometimes.

854
00:59:22.520 --> 00:59:24.021
You two hide.

855
00:59:24.105 --> 00:59:25.940
I'll take care of this.

856
00:59:26.023 --> 00:59:28.150
What are you talkin' about. Irv?
You're drunk.

857
00:59:29.360 --> 00:59:32.905
[sighs]
Ought to make this interesting then.

858
00:59:34.949 --> 00:59:36.158
Aaron Jeffery Cooper!

859
00:59:37.243 --> 00:59:38.828
-Surrender.
-Hide in there.

860
00:59:38.911 --> 00:59:40.371
-[officer] The girl inside…
-Go.

861
00:59:40.454 --> 00:59:42.290
-Go. go.
-…hands on top of your head!

862
00:59:43.666 --> 00:59:44.876
Come on out now.

863
00:59:47.420 --> 00:59:48.963
Mr. Cooper!

864
00:59:54.510 --> 00:59:58.097
Hey. I'm sorry. Wendell. I was mistaken.

865
00:59:58.848 --> 01:00:02.059
I thought I saw the man and the girl.
but I was wrong.

866
01:00:02.143 --> 01:00:04.604
You sounded pretty convinced
on the phone. Irv.

867
01:00:05.605 --> 01:00:12.111
You know. just last month.
I saw this documentary on TV about. uh…

868
01:00:12.195 --> 01:00:15.948
Uh. I-- I-- I can't recall the exact name.

869
01:00:16.032 --> 01:00:19.911
but it was somethin' like
"Walkin' Dreamin'."

870
01:00:20.703 --> 01:00:25.041
There was this guy on there.
dreamt he swallowed a cockroach.

871
01:00:25.124 --> 01:00:28.669
and he jumped up
and made himself puke.

872
01:00:29.629 --> 01:00:30.630
It's all right.

873
01:00:35.426 --> 01:00:36.928
No. Charlie. Charlie.

874
01:00:37.011 --> 01:00:38.930
Hey. stay with me. stay with me.
stay with me.

875
01:00:39.013 --> 01:00:43.017
Just breathe. Breathe.
Breathe. That's right.

876
01:00:44.435 --> 01:00:46.229
I feel something.

877
01:00:46.312 --> 01:00:47.396
What?

878
01:00:49.398 --> 01:00:51.359
Someone's here.

879
01:00:51.609 --> 01:00:54.028
You sayin' you called us out
on account of a dream?

880
01:00:54.111 --> 01:00:56.489
A pretty convincing one too. uh--

881
01:00:56.572 --> 01:01:00.409
Ah. the news was on. I--
I drifted off and…

882
01:01:02.245 --> 01:01:03.871
And I'm drunk.

883
01:01:03.955 --> 01:01:05.581
Wanna know what I think?

884
01:01:06.874 --> 01:01:08.292
Not particularly.

885
01:01:08.376 --> 01:01:12.797
I think we're here. and this man. Cooper.
he's considerably dangerous.

886
01:01:12.880 --> 01:01:16.425
So even if you were just dreamin' it. Irv.
we'd like to search your--

887
01:01:16.509 --> 01:01:17.593
[gunshot]

888
01:01:17.677 --> 01:01:20.012
Shit. shit. Officer down!

889
01:01:20.096 --> 01:01:22.390
-We need backup. now! Now!
-[officer 2] I see him!

890
01:01:23.891 --> 01:01:25.059
The tree line!

891
01:01:26.811 --> 01:01:28.020
[grunts]

892
01:01:44.912 --> 01:01:46.289
[grunts]

893
01:01:46.372 --> 01:01:47.373
Breathe. okay?

894
01:01:47.456 --> 01:01:49.083
-He killed Mommy.
-Just wait. Charlie.

895
01:01:49.166 --> 01:01:51.878
No. Charlie!
Charlie! Charlie! No!

896
01:01:52.920 --> 01:01:54.130
[screams]

897
01:02:03.055 --> 01:02:05.057
[whimpering]

898
01:02:05.808 --> 01:02:06.934
I'm so sorry.

899
01:02:17.820 --> 01:02:18.863
[Andy] Charlie.

900
01:02:18.946 --> 01:02:20.198
Remember what I taught you?

901
01:02:21.991 --> 01:02:23.326
-Keep running.
-Yeah.

902
01:02:33.294 --> 01:02:34.837
I love you. Daddy.

903
01:02:34.921 --> 01:02:36.547
I love you too. sweetheart.

904
01:02:37.048 --> 01:02:39.050
Now. run. Run!

905
01:02:43.679 --> 01:02:44.805
[inhales]

906
01:02:44.889 --> 01:02:46.098
[neck cracks]

907
01:02:53.314 --> 01:02:55.775
[straining]

908
01:02:57.860 --> 01:03:00.488
[groaning]

909
01:03:21.467 --> 01:03:22.718
Very clever.

910
01:03:27.390 --> 01:03:30.184
[gasping]

911
01:03:35.648 --> 01:03:37.650
[gasping continues]

912
01:03:47.952 --> 01:03:48.953
Gotcha.

913
01:04:00.006 --> 01:04:02.341
They will never stop until they have her.

914
01:04:02.425 --> 01:04:03.801
You'll never catch her.

915
01:04:03.885 --> 01:04:05.511
[laughs]

916
01:04:19.901 --> 01:04:21.777
[agent] Lenses in. Lenses in!

917
01:04:22.737 --> 01:04:25.031
[agent on radio] <i>Containment team
has arrived on site.</i>

918
01:04:25.114 --> 01:04:26.490
<i>Beginning perimeter search now.</i>

919
01:04:27.408 --> 01:04:29.994
[agent] Subject's down.
Everybody's down.

920
01:04:30.620 --> 01:04:31.662
Except him.

921
01:04:31.746 --> 01:04:33.456
On your knees! Move in.

922
01:04:33.539 --> 01:04:34.540
[agent 2] Move!

923
01:04:34.624 --> 01:04:36.751
[agent] Careful. He's dangerous.

924
01:04:39.003 --> 01:04:41.088
-[neck cracks]
-Gimme your gun.

925
01:04:41.589 --> 01:04:44.300
No dice. freak. We've got protection.

926
01:04:47.553 --> 01:04:48.763
Any sign of her?

927
01:04:48.846 --> 01:04:50.973
[on radio] <i>Negative.
We're checkin' the other structures.</i>

928
01:04:51.057 --> 01:04:52.600
<i>We found the owners inside.</i>

929
01:04:53.643 --> 01:04:55.645
[dogs barking]

930
01:05:04.195 --> 01:05:07.031
[panting. crying]

931
01:05:21.295 --> 01:05:23.214
You lost her. Rainbird.

932
01:05:23.297 --> 01:05:25.383
You left a trail of dead cops
in your wake.

933
01:05:25.466 --> 01:05:27.218
You call that discretion?

934
01:05:27.301 --> 01:05:28.719
You have the father.

935
01:05:28.803 --> 01:05:31.889
So. she's just gonna what?
She's gonna feel her way here?

936
01:05:31.973 --> 01:05:35.017
They are connected. She will come for him.

937
01:05:37.103 --> 01:05:40.481
Retirement has made you sloppy and soft.

938
01:05:43.359 --> 01:05:45.319
Is that why you blindfold me?

939
01:05:48.823 --> 01:05:51.951
I don't need to see your eyes
to feel your fear.

940
01:05:57.248 --> 01:05:58.916
You don't know what I feel.

941
01:06:01.627 --> 01:06:06.174
She will come for him.
as she will come for us all.

942
01:06:06.757 --> 01:06:08.134
She is my sister.

943
01:06:09.260 --> 01:06:10.928
My mother.

944
01:06:12.847 --> 01:06:14.515
Well. you killed her mother.

945
01:06:16.309 --> 01:06:18.269
She will be your death.

946
01:06:18.352 --> 01:06:20.021
A fate which I deserve.

947
01:06:22.273 --> 01:06:25.443
When you see her.
you will understand.

948
01:06:37.538 --> 01:06:39.582
[Charlie giggles. laughs]

949
01:06:39.665 --> 01:06:41.709
[screaming]

950
01:06:41.792 --> 01:06:43.127
[gasps]

951
01:06:51.594 --> 01:06:55.389
[sniffling. crying]

952
01:07:03.064 --> 01:07:04.315
Where are you. Daddy?

953
01:07:07.443 --> 01:07:08.444
Tell me.

954
01:07:21.749 --> 01:07:23.960
[Hollister] Rise and shine. Mr. McGee.

955
01:07:24.544 --> 01:07:26.087
Or is it Mr. Burton?

956
01:07:26.921 --> 01:07:28.548
Mr. Rozelle?

957
01:07:32.385 --> 01:07:34.220
No more pseudonyms. Cooper.

958
01:07:37.223 --> 01:07:38.808
No more running.

959
01:07:40.309 --> 01:07:41.811
It's just you and me now.

960
01:07:51.279 --> 01:07:52.280
Wake up.

961
01:08:00.246 --> 01:08:01.247
Rainbird.

962
01:08:01.831 --> 01:08:03.666
the man who killed your poor wife.

963
01:08:04.750 --> 01:08:08.087
he believes that you and your daughter.

964
01:08:08.171 --> 01:08:12.091
you have
some kind of a spiritual connection.

965
01:08:13.759 --> 01:08:14.886
Telepathy.

966
01:08:17.054 --> 01:08:19.182
Lot Six is full of surprises.

967
01:08:20.349 --> 01:08:21.725
Tell me where she is.

968
01:08:23.560 --> 01:08:26.856
Charlie is out there all alone.

969
01:08:28.774 --> 01:08:31.277
Without you.
her emotions will get the best of her.

970
01:08:31.359 --> 01:08:33.779
What happens
when she gets upset.

971
01:08:33.863 --> 01:08:35.573
she gets scared?

972
01:08:35.656 --> 01:08:39.577
She is going to blow
some poor bastard to smithereens.

973
01:08:39.660 --> 01:08:41.287
She's gonna be killin' people.

974
01:08:42.371 --> 01:08:44.122
How's she going to live with that?

975
01:08:47.417 --> 01:08:48.419
Bring her here.

976
01:08:52.590 --> 01:08:54.716
What other choice do you have?

977
01:09:19.575 --> 01:09:21.035
[voice echoes]

978
01:09:21.118 --> 01:09:23.496
<i>Charlie! Charlie! Charlie!</i>

979
01:09:23.578 --> 01:09:24.580
Daddy?

980
01:09:28.835 --> 01:09:34.048
-[seagulls squawking]
-[waves lapping]

981
01:10:17.175 --> 01:10:19.218
[bubbling]

982
01:10:42.325 --> 01:10:43.993
I'm coming. Daddy.

983
01:10:45.578 --> 01:10:46.829
I'll find you.

984
01:11:24.116 --> 01:11:25.701
[teenager chattering]

985
01:11:44.387 --> 01:11:47.098
-What happened to your clothes?
-What happened to your face?

986
01:11:56.732 --> 01:11:58.401
Don't you ever bathe. weirdo?

987
01:11:58.484 --> 01:11:59.986
[chuckles]

988
01:12:01.821 --> 01:12:03.114
I'd like your bike.

989
01:12:04.031 --> 01:12:05.449
Please.

990
01:12:16.627 --> 01:12:18.254
What the hell are you doing. Dale?

991
01:12:50.036 --> 01:12:51.662
Which way is the coast?

992
01:12:53.831 --> 01:12:56.375
The coast. dummies. Where the water is.

993
01:13:33.704 --> 01:13:35.706
[waves breaking]

994
01:13:40.002 --> 01:13:43.047
[security chattering on radio]

995
01:13:47.593 --> 01:13:48.594
[sighs]

996
01:13:49.720 --> 01:13:51.639
[person] Let me know
what the final numbers are.

997
01:13:51.722 --> 01:13:53.057
[person 2] All right. will do.

998
01:13:57.562 --> 01:13:59.438
-[beeps]
-[door lock clicks]

999
01:14:00.314 --> 01:14:02.108
[person 3] I mean. how's the nausea today?

1000
01:14:03.276 --> 01:14:04.986
[sighs] Sorry. babe.

1001
01:14:05.820 --> 01:14:07.864
I mean.
first trimester's almost over. right?

1002
01:14:08.406 --> 01:14:10.324
-The light at the end of the tunnel.
-[alarm chirps]

1003
01:14:10.408 --> 01:14:12.910
-Yeah.
-[car door opens. closes]

1004
01:14:12.994 --> 01:14:15.454
All right. I'll see you when I get home.
Love you. Bye.

1005
01:14:19.333 --> 01:14:20.960
[door closes]

1006
01:14:21.961 --> 01:14:22.962
It's you.

1007
01:14:24.797 --> 01:14:26.757
Take your hand off the key.

1008
01:14:28.718 --> 01:14:30.678
Give me your phone.

1009
01:14:34.140 --> 01:14:35.349
And the card.

1010
01:14:44.942 --> 01:14:46.110
Do you have a gun.

1011
01:14:47.945 --> 01:14:49.363
Agent Jules?

1012
01:14:49.447 --> 01:14:53.034
No. I-I'm just a tech.
They don't let us carry guns.

1013
01:14:53.117 --> 01:14:54.702
This says you're an agent.

1014
01:14:56.746 --> 01:14:59.123
We're all agents. It's just a title.

1015
01:14:59.207 --> 01:15:00.416
Is my father inside?

1016
01:15:02.543 --> 01:15:03.544
[door handle jiggles]

1017
01:15:03.628 --> 01:15:04.712
-I don't know.
-Is he?

1018
01:15:04.795 --> 01:15:07.465
I don't know. I swear. okay?
I don't have that kinda clearance.

1019
01:15:08.090 --> 01:15:10.551
-I don't wanna hurt you. sir.
-Please. why are you doing this?

1020
01:15:10.635 --> 01:15:12.386
Is my father inside?

1021
01:15:12.470 --> 01:15:14.430
I don't know! Okay?

1022
01:15:14.514 --> 01:15:16.390
Stop. Please.

1023
01:15:16.474 --> 01:15:19.143
If he's here. he'll be at the bottom.

1024
01:15:19.227 --> 01:15:20.478
Who else is in there?

1025
01:15:21.437 --> 01:15:24.774
Computer techs. scientists.
that kind of thing.

1026
01:15:25.483 --> 01:15:26.651
No long-haired men?

1027
01:15:29.237 --> 01:15:30.696
Answer me!

1028
01:15:31.447 --> 01:15:34.242
Please. just-- Okay. just stay calm.

1029
01:15:34.325 --> 01:15:35.785
-We can work something out.
-Tell me!

1030
01:15:37.036 --> 01:15:38.162
No!

1031
01:15:42.667 --> 01:15:44.669
[panting]

1032
01:15:49.465 --> 01:15:51.217
You said you didn't have a gun.

1033
01:15:52.510 --> 01:15:54.595
[groans]

1034
01:15:56.138 --> 01:15:58.307
I don't wanna hurt anyone. I promised.

1035
01:16:00.434 --> 01:16:01.894
He's in pain. Charlie.

1036
01:16:03.604 --> 01:16:05.398
You have to put him out of his misery.

1037
01:16:07.233 --> 01:16:08.776
This is what it costs.

1038
01:16:20.746 --> 01:16:22.248
What's goin' on?

1039
01:16:23.207 --> 01:16:24.876
Ah. shit.

1040
01:16:25.668 --> 01:16:27.920
-[radio beeps]
-We got a disturbance in the east lot.

1041
01:16:28.546 --> 01:16:29.797
All units stand by.

1042
01:16:30.423 --> 01:16:32.091
-[beeps]
-[door lock clicks]

1043
01:16:40.558 --> 01:16:41.642
[gasps]

1044
01:16:50.985 --> 01:16:52.361
She's inside the building.

1045
01:16:52.445 --> 01:16:54.572
[on radio] <i>Clearing her path
to the restricted level now.</i>

1046
01:17:06.876 --> 01:17:08.127
[gasps]

1047
01:17:09.879 --> 01:17:10.922
What the…

1048
01:17:11.005 --> 01:17:13.341
Ah. come on. come on. come on.

1049
01:17:49.293 --> 01:17:50.294
Daddy.

1050
01:17:56.592 --> 01:17:58.344
-[beeps]
-[door lock clicks]

1051
01:18:01.305 --> 01:18:02.306
[door opens]

1052
01:18:04.267 --> 01:18:05.852
[lock clicks]

1053
01:18:06.727 --> 01:18:08.521
[on radio] <i>She's on the restricted level.</i>

1054
01:18:11.649 --> 01:18:12.984
Come on.

1055
01:18:17.238 --> 01:18:18.948
-[alarm beeps]
-[gasps]

1056
01:18:23.160 --> 01:18:25.204
[on radio]
<i>She's headed your way. Maintain.</i>

1057
01:18:40.011 --> 01:18:41.971
<i>Asset moving down hallway 12.</i>

1058
01:18:43.890 --> 01:18:45.600
<i>Passing her off to beta team.</i>

1059
01:18:46.976 --> 01:18:47.977
<i>We've got her.</i>

1060
01:18:48.895 --> 01:18:50.354
<i>Target visual acquired.</i>

1061
01:18:51.355 --> 01:18:53.399
<i>Securing hallways and doors behind her.</i>

1062
01:18:54.442 --> 01:18:56.444
-[lock clicks]
-<i>She's all yours. Cap.</i>

1063
01:19:04.660 --> 01:19:05.661
Daddy!

1064
01:19:07.288 --> 01:19:08.581
Daddy. wake up!

1065
01:19:11.751 --> 01:19:12.919
Daddy. wake up.

1066
01:19:15.213 --> 01:19:16.214
Charlie?

1067
01:19:17.840 --> 01:19:19.842
Wh-- Why-- Why are you here?

1068
01:19:21.177 --> 01:19:23.221
I came. I got your message.

1069
01:19:24.138 --> 01:19:25.473
[sighs]

1070
01:19:28.226 --> 01:19:29.727
That wasn't me. Charlie.

1071
01:19:33.439 --> 01:19:35.149
[Andy] <i>I would never bring you here.</i>

1072
01:19:37.026 --> 01:19:38.027
<i>That wasn't me.</i>

1073
01:19:39.028 --> 01:19:40.863
But I can get you out.

1074
01:19:40.947 --> 01:19:42.949
No. No. Charlie.

1075
01:19:44.700 --> 01:19:46.077
There's no getting out.

1076
01:19:46.786 --> 01:19:47.787
[groans]

1077
01:19:47.870 --> 01:19:50.414
-There's no getting out for me.
-[Hollister] Charlie.

1078
01:19:51.541 --> 01:19:53.876
It wasn't supposed to be this way.

1079
01:19:55.336 --> 01:19:57.463
It wasn't supposed to be
this difficult.

1080
01:19:59.131 --> 01:20:00.466
Stay calm. dear.

1081
01:20:00.550 --> 01:20:03.636
If you try to burn me.
you'll burn your daddy too.

1082
01:20:04.554 --> 01:20:07.765
My name's Captain Hollister.
but you can call me Cap.

1083
01:20:09.016 --> 01:20:11.102
I run this facility.

1084
01:20:11.185 --> 01:20:12.603
You can trust me. Charlie.

1085
01:20:14.939 --> 01:20:16.816
You'll be safe here. You'll be protected.

1086
01:20:17.483 --> 01:20:20.027
We'll take really good care of you
and your father.

1087
01:20:20.736 --> 01:20:22.405
My dad needs a doctor.

1088
01:20:22.488 --> 01:20:24.532
They've seen him already. Charlie.

1089
01:20:25.783 --> 01:20:30.538
Micro-hemorrhages.
His brain bleeds when he uses his power.

1090
01:20:32.874 --> 01:20:36.961
The same thing could happen to you too.
Charlie. but we can teach you.

1091
01:20:37.879 --> 01:20:40.089
-It's what your mother wanted.
-No.

1092
01:20:40.173 --> 01:20:41.174
No.

1093
01:20:42.967 --> 01:20:47.388
Call a doctor right now
or I'll hurt myself.

1094
01:20:48.306 --> 01:20:49.557
[gasps]

1095
01:20:50.349 --> 01:20:52.185
Don't do it. Charlie. Don't do it.

1096
01:20:55.062 --> 01:20:56.856
Call a doctor right now.

1097
01:20:57.899 --> 01:20:58.900
Do it!

1098
01:21:08.326 --> 01:21:10.161
[jacket rustling]

1099
01:21:12.496 --> 01:21:14.624
[Hollister]
You're a very determined young lady.

1100
01:21:15.208 --> 01:21:17.877
Use it wisely.
It'll take you far in this life.

1101
01:21:18.461 --> 01:21:19.545
I should know.

1102
01:21:19.629 --> 01:21:21.923
You do bad things here. I can feel it.

1103
01:21:22.006 --> 01:21:24.967
No. we do great things.
We make things better here.

1104
01:21:25.051 --> 01:21:28.679
We make people better.
We make them stronger. People like you.

1105
01:21:29.472 --> 01:21:30.806
Haven't you realized?

1106
01:21:31.557 --> 01:21:37.355
You are a real-life superhero.

1107
01:21:38.314 --> 01:21:39.482
Daddy.

1108
01:21:41.234 --> 01:21:42.735
You're very special.

1109
01:21:46.656 --> 01:21:50.493
The world out there.
they don't know how to handle your power.

1110
01:21:52.203 --> 01:21:53.871
Here we can handle it.

1111
01:21:55.540 --> 01:21:57.208
Because we made you.

1112
01:22:01.087 --> 01:22:02.338
Look at your father.

1113
01:22:05.007 --> 01:22:09.595
They say if he does one more push.
it might kill him.

1114
01:22:10.638 --> 01:22:12.181
You need us.

1115
01:22:13.099 --> 01:22:14.851
I don't wanna hurt anyone.

1116
01:22:15.852 --> 01:22:18.646
I know you don't. honey. I know.

1117
01:22:21.607 --> 01:22:25.111
But we can't run anymore.
I need you to break your promise.

1118
01:22:25.903 --> 01:22:27.238
Daddy.

1119
01:22:28.030 --> 01:22:30.324
You have to burn it down.
Starting with us.

1120
01:22:31.617 --> 01:22:32.827
Daddy. what are you…

1121
01:22:33.995 --> 01:22:35.204
[neck cracks]

1122
01:22:35.872 --> 01:22:37.582
[Andy] I'm sorry to make you do this.

1123
01:22:40.418 --> 01:22:42.837
Burn it all down. It's the only way.

1124
01:22:42.920 --> 01:22:44.130
Easy. Easy.

1125
01:22:45.882 --> 01:22:47.592
Burn me. you burn him too.

1126
01:22:50.970 --> 01:22:52.972
[gasping. panting]

1127
01:22:54.140 --> 01:22:56.267
-[flames ignite]
-[Hollister gasps]

1128
01:22:57.602 --> 01:22:59.604
[Hollister screaming]

1129
01:23:05.276 --> 01:23:06.277
Shit.

1130
01:23:07.236 --> 01:23:08.863
Cap's down.

1131
01:23:08.946 --> 01:23:11.949
We got a fire in the restricted area.
Call in the containment team.

1132
01:23:30.259 --> 01:23:33.346
[agents shouting]

1133
01:23:33.429 --> 01:23:36.140
[on loudspeaker]
<i>Evacuate all non-military staff.</i>

1134
01:23:42.480 --> 01:23:44.774
<i>Evacuate all non-military staff.</i>

1135
01:23:45.942 --> 01:23:49.362
-[all devices beeping]
-[all door locks clicking]

1136
01:23:51.614 --> 01:23:54.200
[on loudspeaker]
<i>Evacuate all non-military staff.</i>

1137
01:23:54.283 --> 01:23:55.785
[alarm buzzes]

1138
01:24:01.040 --> 01:24:03.459
<i>Evacuate all non-military staff.</i>

1139
01:24:04.877 --> 01:24:05.878
[grunts]

1140
01:24:09.382 --> 01:24:11.509
[guard grunts. groans]

1141
01:24:19.600 --> 01:24:21.018
-Stop there.
-It's over.

1142
01:24:21.102 --> 01:24:22.478
[both screaming]

1143
01:24:27.942 --> 01:24:30.444
-[gun clicks]
-[grunts]

1144
01:24:33.030 --> 01:24:34.282
Surrender!

1145
01:24:49.005 --> 01:24:51.924
Please. please.
I don't wanna hurt you.

1146
01:24:52.008 --> 01:24:53.593
I-I can help you.

1147
01:24:53.676 --> 01:24:54.719
My name's Gail.

1148
01:24:56.679 --> 01:24:57.805
I--

1149
01:24:57.889 --> 01:25:01.017
I can lead you out of here to safety.
Mmm?

1150
01:25:01.100 --> 01:25:02.101
Just come with me.

1151
01:25:02.727 --> 01:25:05.563
-[screams]
-[gasps]

1152
01:25:06.772 --> 01:25:07.773
Please.

1153
01:25:15.448 --> 01:25:17.533
Please. Please. No. no. Please. please.

1154
01:25:17.617 --> 01:25:21.412
Liar. liar. pants on fire.

1155
01:25:21.495 --> 01:25:23.664
No!

1156
01:25:32.757 --> 01:25:33.758
[door opens]

1157
01:25:40.389 --> 01:25:42.725
[Charlie screaming]

1158
01:25:55.696 --> 01:25:57.198
[screaming]

1159
01:26:19.929 --> 01:26:20.930
We got her.

1160
01:26:26.143 --> 01:26:28.062
-It's okay. Charlie.
-[gunshot]

1161
01:27:25.620 --> 01:27:27.997
[crackling]

1162
01:28:32.019 --> 01:28:34.021
[explosions continue]

1163
01:29:02.049 --> 01:29:05.052
[waves breaking]

